      <gmd:abstract>
        <gco:CharacterString>The FAO initiative on soil nutrient mapping using digital soil mapping is a critical step in the development of a Global Soil Nutrient and Soil Nutrient Budget Map (GSNmap). This capacity building programme is led by FAO's Global Soil Partnership (GSP) to increase awareness and understanding of the importance of soil health and promote sustainable soil management practices. The initiative has already successfully reached 60 countries and trained 274 people in NENA, Asian, African, Eurasian, and Latin American regions.</gco:CharacterString>
      </gmd:abstract>
